UTC - cordinated universal time

# To determine which zonen is we are on
$ date

# To show utc time
$ date -u

# There is a specific command we can use timedatectl
$ man timedatectl

# To list all availale timezones
$ timedatectl list-timezones

# To set TimeZone
$ timedatectl set-timezone Asia/Kolkata

# One important file which could be helpfll
$ /etc/localtime   # it's just a symlink which points too
$ /usr/share/zonesinfo
$ /etc/timezone		# Holds timezone information for many zones But not for all systems

# we can also use this one commannd
$ man tzselect
